        "## Part-of-speech (POS) Tagging"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "02d28218",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "02d28218"
      },
      "source": [
        "I tried to use pyarabicand NLTK and found that NLTK pos_tag only supports English and Russian "
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 34,
      "id": "58a458f9",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "58a458f9"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "from pyarabic.araby import strip_tashkeel\n",
        "from pyarabic.araby import tokenize as arabic_tokenize\n",
        "from nltk import pos_tag\n",
        "nltk.download('averaged_perceptron_tagger')\n",
        "\n",
        "def pos_tag_arabic_text(text):\n",
        "    words = arabic_tokenize(strip_tashkeel(text))\n",
        "    tagged_words = pos_tag(words, lang='ar')\n",
        "    tagged_sentence = \" \".join([f\"{word}/{tag}\" for word, tag in tagged_words])\n",
        "    return tagged_sentence\n",
        "data_cleaned['pos_tags'] = data_cleaned['text'].apply(pos_tag_arabic_text)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "8a3c3e28",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "8a3c3e28"
      },
      "source": [
        "Then I tried farasa and got some errors regarding its modules such as that the Farasa library for Arabic NLP does not have a specific module for POS tagging. Instead, it provides a morphological analyzer and a segmenter which can be used to extract POS tags from the morphological analysis."
      ]
    },
